s, which may be explained by the\nlatitude-dependent wind structure of eta Car. The quick and strong recovery of\nthe HeII emission in 2014 supports a scenario, in which the wind-wind shock may\nnot have completely collapsed as was proposed for previous events. All this may\nbe the consequence of just one elementary change, namely a strong decrease in\nthe primary's mass-loss rate.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Apr 2015 05:35:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
